                    <span>This book is one of the few you would like to have in your library. <BR> a. It compresses the TCP/IP working in short and sweet format. <BR> b. It's tip section has lot of sub tips/information which mention differences/workarounds etc in concise way. <BR> c. It has extensive hands on samples to refer to.<BR> d. It feels like culmination of real life hands on implementation of protocol suite and its usage in day to day life which author succintly conveys to readers in form of anecdotes/ideas etc.<BR> e. Author is very precise about what book is not and thus maintains the readable/digestible size of the book and refers to comer/steven when appropriate.<BR> f. It will be useful for every software eng to understand the workings and sometimes even pick cool concepts from the most scalable app ever designed (TCP/IP).<BR><P>Overall the best book buy...most of the effective series have been good.</span>
                  
