                    <span>The book is very useful for TCP/IP programmers especially in Unix environment. It presents the core programming techniques very clearly. However, running the codes in Windows platform is very hectic and time consuming. The author mentions the words Windows, winsock very weakly in the book just to get the attention of also Windows user, I believe.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">buy it even if you own Stevens' book</div>
