                    <span>This book has a perfect balance of brevity and depth. Anything shorter would have been superficial, anything deeper would begin to compete with Stevens' Unix Network Programming (and lose). As is, this book fits very well for developers who do occasional TCP/IP development, but still need to develop reliable, industrial-grade software.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">only way for me to learn C/C++ sockets</div>
                    <div>
