                    <span>I couldn't find any good examples or documentation on the web that made sockets easy enough for me to implement in C/C++. But Snader's book explained it thoroughly and moreover simply enough for me to understand and emulate, and lo and behold, I had my first socket program running on windows and *nix in about a week. It also does a great job of introducing protocols and TCP/IP/UDP specifically. I have only read the first half but I am sure the second half is just as good. That is all I needed, since I just needed an understanding of sockets to get going. I highly recommend this book to intermediate programmers who want to get into network programming and networking in general.</span>
                  
